National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location: CUT BANK, MT
Accident Number: DEN87LA205
Date & Time: 08/01/1987, 1320 MDT
Registration: N9748T
Aircraft: CESSNA 172C
Aircraft Damage: Substantial
Defining Event:
Injuries: 2 None
Flight Conducted Under: Part 91: General Aviation - Personal
 Analysis THE PLT STATED THAT SHE RADIOED THE CUT BANK FSS AND WAS TOLD THAT THE WIND WAS 060 DEGREES AT 41 KNOTS.
SHE THEN LANDED THE ACFT UNEVENTFULLY.
HOWEVER, WHILE TURNING 90 DEGREES OFF THE RWY ONTO A TAXIWAY, THE ACFT NOSED OVER.
Probable Cause and Findings The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be: Findings Occurrence #1: NOSE OVER Phase of Operation: TAXI - FROM LANDING Findings 1.
(F) WEATHER CONDITION - HIGH WIND 2.
(F) WEATHER CONDITION - GUSTS 3.
(F) WEATHER CONDITION - UNFAVORABLE WIND 4.
(C) IN-FLIGHT PLANNING/DECISION - IMPROPER - PILOT IN COMMAND 5.
